The paper discusses the development of a time-aware exploratory search system for scholars, which involves information retrieval, natural language processing, and human-computer interaction. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), followed by cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also mentions entity filters, which suggests a possible connection to cs.CL (Computational Linguistics) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
